_As a user, I want only active litters displayed in cages and litter counts._

+Acceptance Criteria+:
* Cages only display active litters. (fixed in COMA-1937)
* On the litters list, filter for active litters by default.
* Dashboard counts take active litter into consideration when displaying count on:
*# Litters box on the dashboard
*# Strain cards on the dashboard
*# Strain dashboard's litter count


For future reference here is the logic/code currently used int he iOS app:

Display litter in cage if litter.IsActive()== true

{code:applescript}
litter.IsActive() = (litter.dateWeaned == nil && litter.hasLivingOffspring())

(BOOL)hasLivingOffspring {

BOOL hasLivingOffspring = NO;
        // Scenario: No pups recorded yet (and no pups generated)
    if (self.numberOfPups.intValue == 0 && self.offspring.count == 0){
        hasLivingOffspring = YES;
    } else if (self.numberOfPups.intValue > 0 && self.offspring.count == 0 && (self.foundDeadCount.intValue +self.missingCount.intValue) < self.numberOfPups.intValue){
        hasLivingOffspring = YES;
    } else if (self.offspring.count > 0){

        for (MouseEntity *mouse in self.offspring) {
            if (mouse.deathDate == nil){
                hasLivingOffspring = YES;
                break;
            }
        }

    }

    return hasLivingOffspring;
{code}

